#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.155"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.155:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.155:0.2"
msgid "15. Navapurāṇavagga"
msgstr "15. The Old and the New"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 155. Dhammakathikapucchasutta → kammakathikasuttaṃ (bj) | kathika (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.155:0.3"
msgid "155. Dhammakathikapucchasutta"
msgstr "155. A Dhamma Speaker"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.141"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.155:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn35.155:1.2"
msgid "“‘dhammakathiko, dhammakathiko’ti, bhante, vuccati."
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of a ‘Dhamma speaker’."

msgctxt "sn35.155:1.3"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, dhammakathiko hotī”ti?"
msgstr "How is a Dhamma speaker defined?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Cakkhussa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, ‘"
"dhammakathiko bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"“If a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment, dispassion, and "
"cessation regarding the eye, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who "
"speaks on Dhamma’."

msgctxt "sn35.155:2.2"
msgid ""
"Cakkhussa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti, ‘"
"dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"If they practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding "
"the eye, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who practices in line "
"with the teaching’."

msgctxt "sn35.155:2.3"
msgid ""
"Cakkhussa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādāvimutto hoti, ‘"
"diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya … pe …"
msgstr ""
"If they’re freed by not grasping by disillusionment, dispassion, and "
"cessation regarding the eye, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who "
"has attained extinguishment in this very life’."

msgctxt "sn35.155:2.4"
msgid ""
"jivhāya ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, ‘"
"dhammakathiko bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya … pe …"
msgstr ""
"If a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment with the ear … nose … "
"tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.155:2.5"
msgid ""
"manassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, ‘"
"dhammakathiko bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"mind, for its fading away and cessation, they’re qualified to be called a ‘"
"mendicant who speaks on Dhamma’."

msgctxt "sn35.155:2.6"
msgid ""
"Manassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti, ‘"
"dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"If they practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding "
"the mind, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who practices in line "
"with the teaching’."

msgctxt "sn35.155:2.7"
msgid ""
"Manassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādāvimutto hoti, ‘"
"diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"If they’re freed by not grasping by disillusionment, dispassion, and "
"cessation regarding the mind, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant "
"who has attained extinguishment in this very life’.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.8"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.9"
msgid "Navapurāṇavaggo pañcamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.155:3.1"
msgid "Kammaṃ cattāri sappāyā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:3.2"
msgid "anantevāsi kimatthiyā;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:3.3"
msgid "Atthi nu kho pariyāyo,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:3.4"
msgid "indriyakathikena cāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.155:3.5"
msgid "Saḷāyatanavagge tatiyapaṇṇāsako samatto."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="vagguddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.155:4.1"
msgid "Yogakkhemi ca loko ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:4.2"
msgid "Gahapati devadahena ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:4.3"
msgid "Navapurāṇena paṇṇāso,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:4.4"
msgid "Tatiyo tena vuccatīti."
msgstr ""
